            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Compulsive Hunger",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "Despite being undead, a gaki is plagued by an insatiable hunger, and believes it can gain a normal body or rest in peace if it consumes the right mixture of flesh, food, and drink. A gaki that finds a corpse or is offered food, wine, holy water, or flowers must succeed at a DC 20 Will save or spend one turn trying to grab and consume it. Its narrow neck prevents it from swallowing more than a tiny amount, and it gives up after 1 round of attempting to do so. A gaki that consumes holy water in this way is not harmed by it."
